div.p:
3. In these circumstances it was impossible for the Protocol Committee, as such, to submit any document for consideration by the Council at their meeting to-day. In order that the Council may have some document as a basis for their discussion at to-day’s meeting, I put forward—on my own responsibility—alternative drafts of a Protocol—
C.F.M.(45) 72Not printed.—arranged by subject matter, on the model of recent Protocols, but using to the fullest possible extent the language of the agreed Daily Record of Decisions;
C.F.M.(45) 73Not printed.—an arrangement of the agreed Daily Record of Decisions, chronologically under subject headings, in accordance with the suggestion at 1 (c) above.
